<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,150,1402]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,150,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[414,511,151,177]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[414,511,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Sauresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have (1) claw sheath, present, (2) contact between the nasal and rostral scales, absent, (3) scales in contact with the nasal scale, four, (4) postnasal scales, one, (5) position of the nostril in the nasal scale, central, (6) keels on dorsal body scales, absent, (7) digits per limb, four, (8) longest toe lamellae, 8–12, (9) dorsal scale rows, 101–127, (10) relative head width, 9.36–12.2, (11) relative rostral height, 41.3–66.2, (12) relative frontonasal length, 1.70–2.56, (13) relative interparietal distance, 0–0.431, (14) relative axilla-groin distance 63.9–69.9.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,150,1402]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
From 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[266,361,367,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[266,361,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[367,471,367,393]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[367,471,367,393]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[652,749,367,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[652,749,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Sauresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the digits per limb (four versus five in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1215,1310,367,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1215,1310,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1316,1420,367,393]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1316,1420,367,393]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), the longest toe lamellae (8–12 versus 16–17), the dorsal scale rows (101–127 versus 96), the distance between the parietal scales (0–0.431 versus 0.632), and the relative axilla-groin distance (63.9–69.9 versus 60.0). From 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,261,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Caribicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,261,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Caribicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[271,379,475,501]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[271,379,475,501]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[569,666,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,666,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Sauresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the claw sheath (present versus absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1193,1303,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Caribicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1193,1303,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Caribicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1312,1420,475,501]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1312,1420,475,501]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), keels on the dorsal body scales (absent versus their presence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[877,987,511,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Caribicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[877,987,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Caribicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[995,1102,511,537]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[995,1102,511,537]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), digits per limb (four versus five), relative frontonasal length (1.70–2.56 versus 2.98–3.32), and the distance between the parietal scales (0– 0.431 versus 0.468–1.42). From 
<emphasis box="[523,625,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1839" box="[523,620,583,609]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Celestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Celestus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[807,904,583,609]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[807,904,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Sauresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1839" box="[182,277,619,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Celestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,277,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Celestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the digits per limb (four versus five). From 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[852,952,619,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Comptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[852,952,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Comptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[961,1068,619,645]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[961,1068,619,645]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[1258,1355,619,645]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1355,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Sauresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[626,726,655,681]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Comptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[626,726,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Comptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,839,655,681]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[733,839,655,681]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), keels on the dorsal body scales (absent versus their presence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[283,383,691,717]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Comptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[283,383,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Comptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[389,494,691,717]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[389,494,691,717]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), digits per limb (four versus five), the longest toe lamellae (8–12 versus 13–23), the relative frontonasal length (1.70–2.56 versus 2.95–3.65), and the relative axilla-groin distance (63.9–69.9 versus 51.9–60.0). From 
<emphasis box="[353,479,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1862" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1862" box="[353,476,763,789]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Panolopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Panolopus</taxonomicName>
,
