we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[654,751,763,789]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[654,751,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Sauresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1862" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1862" box="[1300,1420,763,789]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Panolopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1300,1420,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Panolopus</emphasis>
